article.headline: Old Dominion 81, James Madison 43
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Gerald Lee scored 18 points and Old Dominion beat James Madison 81-43 on Thursday night in the semifinals of the inaugural CollegeInsider.com tournament. Frank Hassell had 16 points and 13 rebounds for the Monarchs (24-10), who will travel to Bradley for Tuesday's tournament final. Marsharee Neely made four of six 3-pointers and finished with 14 points. "To have so many kids play well on the same night and play so hard and so together, that's really fun for me, in my role, to see it kind of come together like that," Monarchs coach Blaine Taylor said. Old Dominion made eight of its first 12 shots to build a 21-4 lead. "We forced a lot of shots and rushed them the last couple of games, so we just wanted to calm our minds down and just take our time," Neely said. "It was just one of those days." Devon Moore scored 13 for the Dukes (21-15), who shot 31 percent from the field and were outrebounded 51-21. It was James Madison's worst loss since a 93-52 setback against Texas A&M-Corpus Christi on Dec. 30, 2005. "They were better than us tonight at every position," said Juwann James, who finished with 10 points. "They came out and threw the first punch, and we didn't bounce back." Old Dominion and James Madison split two Colonial Athletic Association games this season. The Dukes shot 67 percent in a 70-62 win in Norfolk, and the Monarchs won 80-74 in Harrisonburg.
